AGI - Weddings in the prison of Civitavecchia between Mario Pincarelli - sentenced to 21 years for the murder of Willy Monteiro Duarte - and a 28-year-old in the province of Rome who fell in love with him seeing him in the news. The bride arrived on a 500 in pink meat dress and with a black handkerchief to cover the face from the cameras. At the wedding, celebrated with civil rite, present the relatives of both spouses. Pincarelli's Witness his lawyer - the criminalist Loredana Mazzenga - who assisted him during the trial and his relative.
&nbsp;
Of this marriage "he said he wanted to have this experience, nothing more", explained lawyer Mazzenga entering prison. Speaking of Willy's judicial and death, the criminal claimed that "Pincarelli always had a word for Willy's family. Since the days after the affair, Pincarelli has written letters to the victim's family. It was the only one among the defendants who more than apologize expressed closeness to this fact. Rather than approaching these words, this boy could not do."
&nbsp;
Mazzenga also said that "there was a sentence and this boy is expiating the punishment" at 21 years and that the marriage will not lead Pincarelli to have "reward permits". There is no lack of tension. Before the beginning of the celebration, outside the penitentiary, one of the companions of the bride, probably a relative, hurled against the journalists inveendo, insulting and spitting towards the photographers. The situation is then back to normal.

