AGI -&nbsp;Palazzo dei Marescialli becomes Palazzo Bachelet. The Csm, with a deliberation approved on 7 February, has in fact decided to intitulate to Vittorio Bachelet the palace in which the autonomous governing body of the judiciary has its headquarters. This morning the ceremony will take place in the presence of the President of the Republic Sergio Mattarella, during which the jurist will be remembered by the son, Professor Giovanni Bachelet, the vice president of the Csm Fabio Pinelli and the president emerita of the Constitutional Court Marta Cartabia.
<br> Bachelet, killed by the Red Brigades on 12 February 1980, has since 1976 been the vice president of the Higher Council of the judiciary: "He was convinced defender of the principles of the Constitutional Charter", "the assertor of dialogue", recalls the Csm, underlining that "I seek a high synthesis among the different cultural sensibilities expressed by the Higher Council. Ideal even more precious in tragic years such as those of terrorism and the crucial challenges posed to the rule of law that called the republican institutions, and among them the judiciary at the forefront, to the commitment agreed against the ever-invasive threat".
&nbsp;
At the end of the ceremony, the bronze altarpiece, created by the sculptor Giuseppe Ducrot, depicting Bachelet and will be placed at the main entrance of the palace. A volume was dedicated to "Palazzo Bachelet", with a preface by Massimiliano Fuksas: contains an introductory written by President Mattarella, a contribution by Vice President Pinelli and texts by professors Luigi Gallo, curator of the volume, and Carla Benocci, on the historical and architectural events of the palace: the volume is illustrated by the photos of Alberto Novelli.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2> The memory of Sergio Mattarella</h2>
"Being a man of dialogue has been, from the very beginning, the characteristic of his political and social activity." Sergio Mattarella thus recalls Vittorio Bachelet in his intervention on the occasion of the intitulation of the building seat of the Csm to his memory. Report, the Head of State, that Bachelet "already in 1946, at twenty years, as a student, leader of the Fuci always looked for the dialectical comparison with the other university components in view of the reconstruction of democratic Italy: "With none of our fellows, he wrote, we have the right to refuse or to be lazy in throwing the bridge" and emphasizes the value of today's ceremony - thanking the Vice-President and the Csm for this decision "assuming to keep alive the memory of his service in the institutions and to renew the gratitude for his commitment" - reasserting that Bachelet "also as vice president of the Higher Council, has been authentic witness of the values of our Constitution. He was constantly working for the search for shared perspectives also in view of the ideological fractures that crossed our country."
&nbsp;
The dialogue, then, "was always a distinctive feature of his commitment to society throughout the entire span of his life, in Catholic organizations, in teaching in the classrooms of the university, in the Higher Council of judiciary, in every other public activity. Dialogue - Mattarella repeats - represented for him, more than a method, the essence of democracy". &nbsp;
&nbsp;
"The search for comparison - the President of the Republic resumes - was not easy and, sometimes, by some even appreciated, in a season among the most tormented and conflicting of the republican history, where not only the words and ideologies were made more harsh, but the violence of the weapons claimed to be an instrument of political struggle, raising criminal groups to political subject.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
In those dramatic years, Vittorio Bachelet expressed the conviction that the strengthening of democratic institutions would not be achieved through confrontation, but with choices, as far as possible shared, of full and consistent implementation of the principles of our Constitution".
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
"The evening before the brutal assassination - he recalls - accompanying his friend Achille Ardigo's home, had discussed with him the terrorist threat, reaching the conclusion, shared, that terrorism should be fought without renouncing the principles of democratic legality, in compliance with constitutional rules, without resorting to arbitrary, as the Republic has resources able to prevail the values of the Constitution even in the most critical times". it was this exemplary coherence to mark its commitment, always of great value, in every area," he notes.&nbsp;
