AGI - Return to the classroom the massacre of &nbsp;Erba and is the day of the defense of Olindo Romano and Rosa Bazzi who wants to&nbsp;convince the Court of Appeal of Brescia on the foundation of the "new evidence" that would be able to demolish the sentence to the life sentence of the couple deemed guilty of the massacre occurred on December 11, 2006 when they lost their neighboring son Thus, we go back to talk &nbsp; the cornerstones of the judgment passed in judgment: the confession of the spouses; the testimony of Mario Frigerio, survived for a malformation to the carotid; the blood trail belonging to Valeria Cherubini on Olindo's car. So much flesh on fire, so, to the point that it is difficult to think that the decision of the court can arrive already in the day. Olindo and Rosa are seated in the cage reserved to the defendants: He wears a gray sweater, she has a black jacket. The court, before giving way to the debate, has arranged the ban on shooting with mobile phones. &nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;
"Our advices describe a dynamic of the facts completely different from the judgment that makes incompatible the presence of Olindo and Rosa with the massacre of&nbsp;Erba", is the debut of lawyer Fabio Schembri who assists the couple together with his colleagues Nico D'Ascola, Patrizia Morello and Luisa Bordeaux. Schembri, in particular, mentions the advice on the death of Cherubini that would be hit in his house, and not on the stairs, as emerges from the judgment of which the revision is asked, in the moments when the first neighbors tried to rescue Mario Frigerio, the only survivor. "It's a science fiction hypothesis - says the defender - that the woman could climb the stairs after the blow to the skull and for its physical conditions in general."
&nbsp;
And precisely on the testimony of the survivor, the defense of Olindo and Rosa identifies "grave facts and omissions and very serious anomalies". In the course of his short surrender, Schembri argues that "Frigerio the first days did not remember anything and it is not true that he recognized Olindo on December 26 when he was in the hospital, a period in which his conditions were desperate and had a total lack of memory. The new evidence shows that on that occasion anterograde amnesia had reached its peak." Schembri points out that the advice emerges a "false memory after a cognitive deficit and that he was unable to testify".
&nbsp;
The concept also reiterated by D'Ascola, according to which the recognition by Frigerio di Olindo "is a suspect test". At first - it reiterates - the eyewitness describes the killer as "an unknown with olive skin", only after he finds it in the neighbor. "The recognition of a known person - argues D'Ascola also on the basis of new consultations - is automatic and incoercibilical, there is no need to think about it."
&nbsp;
There is no lack of tension between the defendants' defenders and the prosecution. At a certain point D'Ascola invited the Attorney of the State Domenico Chiaro and Fr Guido Rispoli to "avoid plaque manifestations of dissent". "We didn't make a move when you spoke," the lawyer said, seeing the magistrates express disappointment, shaking the boss, for some passages of his argument. The prosecutor's magistrates did not like a passage from D'Ascola on the eyewitness. "There are extremely important interceptions in which Frigerio tells the children not to remember anything" these the words of the lawyer who, alluding to the skepticism manifested by the magistrates also on this point, attacked: "Isn't it? We noticed certain attitudes in the last hearing. We're not born yesterday." &nbsp;
&nbsp;
In the previous hearing of March 1, the public prosecutors had been very firm in asking the judges to declare "inammissible" the requests for revision of the defence and the pg of Milan Cuno Tarfusser. "The truth has already been written and we hope that it will soon be confirmed and that we no longer have to talk about this massacre but remember the victims," said lawyer Massimo Campa, lawyer of the Chestnut family, before the beginning of the hearing.&nbsp;
